Appendix C: Simulation and Validation Pipeline

C.1 Digital Twin Generation

High-fidelity digital twins of lunar south pole regions are constructed from:

1. LRO LOLA (Lunar Orbiter Laser Altimeter): 5m/pixel topography
2. LRO NAC (Narrow Angle Camera): 0.5m/pixel optical imagery
3. Diviner thermal maps: Temperature distributions
4. LEND neutron data: Hydrogen (water ice) probability maps

C.2 Monte Carlo Simulation Framework

Simulation Parameters Sampled:

· Initial rover position (±100m)
· Solar elevation angle (1.5°–5°)
· Regolith properties (cohesion, friction angle)
· Sensor noise levels (1–3× nominal)
· Communication blackout durations (1–24 hours)
· Scientific target distribution (randomized based on LEND data)

Metrics Collected per Run:

· Total scientific value collected (normalized)
· Energy efficiency (km/kWh)
· Safety violations (battery < 15%, temperature excursions)
· Autonomy percentage (distance traveled without human intervention)
· Communication efficiency (bits transmitted per joule)

C.3 Benchmark Comparison

LCAS will be compared against baseline architectures:

Baseline Description Source
Human-in-the-loop Traditional command sequence with 2.6s delay Current operations model
Behavior Trees ROS2 Behavior Trees with hand-coded safety rules Standard autonomy approach
Pure POMDP Full POMDP without hierarchical decomposition Research baseline
Reactive Sense-act loops without planning Minimal autonomy

