---

Appendix I: Prior Art and Literature Review

I.1 Planetary Rover Autonomy

Work Contribution Gap Addressed by LCAS
NASA Mars Rovers (MER, MSL, Perseverance) Visual odometry, hazard detection, autonomous navigation Limited to short horizons, no mission-level reasoning
ESA Rosalind Franklin Autonomous navigation with local maps Similar limitations, Earth-dependent for science targeting
DARPA FANG Autonomous ground vehicles Terrestrial focus, different environment constraints
JPL Autonomous Science Onboard science target detection Reactive, no generative world model

I.2 Cognitive Architectures for Robotics

Work Contribution Gap Addressed by LCAS
CLARAty (NASA JPL) Layered robotics architecture Procedural, limited learning
ROS2 Behavior Trees Modular task sequencing No formal safety guarantees
Soar/R-CAST Cognitive architectures Not designed for extreme environments
DeepMind's Dreamer Latent space planning Unverified, not safety-critical

I.3 Formal Methods in Robotics

Work Contribution Gap Addressed by LCAS
Control Barrier Functions (Ames et al.) Safety-critical control Not integrated with high-level reasoning
POMDP solvers (DESPOT, SARSOP) Planning under uncertainty Computational cost, no safety constraints
Reachability analysis (CORA, Flow*) Verification of dynamical systems Limited to low-dimensional systems
Neural-Symbolic AI Hybrid learning+reasoning Not applied to planetary robotics

